setCapabilityFilter

void setCapabilityFilter(String... capabilityFilter)
Tell WURFL to use only the specified capability set. Notice that this operation is optional.
This method by default does not cause the WURFL database model to be reloaded with the new filtering setup; you need to call this before initialization (which is lazy, and it is performed before the first query), or before reloading the model with one of the dedicated reload methods.

Parameters:
capabilityFilter - The chosen capabilities.

setCapabilityFilter

void setCapabilityFilter(Collection<String> capabilityFilter)
Tell WURFL to use only the specified capability set. Notice that this operation is optional.
This method by default does not cause the WURFL database model to be reloaded with the new filtering setup; you need to call this before initialization (which is lazy, and it is performed before the first query), or before reloading the model with one of the dedicated reload methods.

Parameters:
capabilityFilter - The chosen capabilities.
